projects.name: Security SIEM Learning Roadmap
projects.description: Complete learning roadmap from foundations to production-ready MVP (18-24 months)

tasks.title: Learn Rust: Ownership, Borrowing, Lifetimes
tasks.description: Master Rust's core memory safety concepts including ownership rules, borrowing references, and lifetime annotations

tasks.title: Learn Rust: Structs, Enums, Traits
tasks.description: Understand Rust data structures: structs for custom types, enums for variants, and traits for shared behavior

tasks.title: Learn Rust: Error Handling (Result, Option)
tasks.description: Master error handling with Result<T, E> and Option<T> types, the ? operator, and error propagation

tasks.title: Learn Rust: Pattern Matching
tasks.description: Learn match expressions, if let, while let, and destructuring patterns

tasks.title: Learn Rust: Modules and Crates
tasks.description: Understand module system, visibility rules, cargo workspaces, and publishing crates

tasks.title: Learn Rust: Generics
tasks.description: Master generic types, trait bounds, and monomorphization

tasks.title: Learn Rust: Macros Basics
tasks.description: Learn declarative macros (macro_rules!) and when to use procedural macros

tasks.title: Learn Rust: Testing
tasks.description: Unit tests, integration tests, test organization, mocking strategies

tasks.title: Async Rust: async/await Syntax
tasks.description: Understand async functions, await points, and how futures work

tasks.title: Async Rust: Tokio Runtime
tasks.description: Master the Tokio async runtime, task spawning, and runtime configuration

tasks.title: Async Rust: Futures and Tasks
tasks.description: Deep dive into Future trait, Pin, and task scheduling

tasks.title: Async Rust: Channels (mpsc, broadcast)
tasks.description: Learn async communication with mpsc, oneshot, broadcast, and watch channels

tasks.title: Systems: Process Management
tasks.description: Creating, monitoring, and terminating processes programmatically

tasks.title: Systems: File System Operations
tasks.description: File handling, directory traversal, permissions, and metadata

tasks.title: Systems: Memory Management
tasks.description: Understanding stack vs heap, memory allocation, and memory-mapped files

tasks.title: Systems: System Calls
tasks.description: Direct OS interaction, syscall wrappers, and platform abstractions

tasks.title: Systems: Inter-Process Communication
tasks.description: Pipes, shared memory, sockets, and message passing

tasks.title: Windows: API Basics
tasks.description: Windows API fundamentals, handles, and Win32 programming

tasks.title: Windows: Registry Access
tasks.description: Reading/writing registry keys, monitoring registry changes

tasks.title: Windows: Services Creation

tasks.title: Windows: Firewall API
